	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 11th 3:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>/agree. I have never had a problem with getting a group. Ever. I see many other people who do. Unfortunately, I have heard a lot of bad things about wizards being in a group. I don't know what they are talking about. I can't tell you the number of times I have saved a tanks life because of a well placed nuke to kill the mob or make him run, or a stun that gives the cleric enough time to get that heal spell off. My guess is that there are a few bad players out there that have ruined the rep for every other wizard in the game. In fact, I find grouping much more rewarding (and faster exp) than soloing because the pulls are so much faster. Sure, each individual mob may not give me as much exp, but in my experience, grouping is faster exp than soloing every time. Medding takes a long time, plus you don't die nearly as often or train other people running to the zone because of resists. Perhaps that's where the bad rep comes from. Anyway, enough ranting. The bottom line is to have fun, so do what makes you have fun. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
